OL,3,CMajority vote to establish climate
OL,4,Ccomissioner despite cost concern
OL,6,F"It's regrettable that the DUP have
OL,7,Ftaken this square earth mentality
OL,8,Fagain and voted against the
OL,9,Fregulations, but they have went
OL,10,Fthrough nonetheless and I very much
OL,11,Fwelcome that."
OL,13,FAsked about DUP concerns around the
OL,14,Fcost, Ms O'Neill responded: "What's
OL,15,Fthe cost of doing nothing?
OL,17,F"The cost of doing nothing is
OL,18,Fcontinuing floods, the cost of doing
OL,19,Fnothing is the real implications that
OL,20,Fpeople face, if you take the issues of
OL,21,Fthe fire or the issue of Lough Neagh.
